content.description: This is a new route so the rock is fairly dirty.  Large variety of holds as the rock runs semi-jagged all the wall to the chains.
content.location: Located between Born to Rock and Two Minute Crack.

content.description: Nasty large crack going along the left dihedral of Rock-A-Bye Baby chimney/arete.
content.protection: Large variety of gear.  Can get some small stuff in way back there.  Bring lots of runners.  Shares anchors with Rock-A-Bye Baby.
content.location: Large crack just left of Rock-A-Bye Baby

content.description: Thin crack, lots of finger sized stuff.  Slightly overhung start, 2 great ledges to rest on.  Crux is right before the 2nd ledge where the crack gets really tiny and the face is less feartured.  Stick through it and reach for large jugs right over the ledge.
content.protection: I went up this with a couple of nuts and stoppers.  If you use camalots, I don't think you would need anything bigger than a .75.
content.location: Thin crack to the right of the obvious arete going up the east face.  Shares the same chains as Rock-A-Bye Baby.

content.description: Rock-A-Bye Baby is by far the most popular route on the crag mainly because it is easy and stands out from other climbs.  Follow arete/chimney through jugs and pockets. Things get a bit slick and crimpy right before the roof.  The crux is either the obvious roof two-thirds the way up or the first 15 ft of the climb.  You can get over the roof by pulling into a large undercling and reaching over for hidden jugs.  Be careful using the undercling as it seems a bit loose.  Possibly an easier way over the roof is to use the crack 3 feet to the right.  Due to the polished rock from all the traffic, this route is tricky for the first few bolts, but I still wouldn't give it a 5.10a.
content.protection: 4 bolts to chains.  If you don't like runouts, bring a nut to put into the crack once you're over the roof otherwise you'll have 15 ft of rope out by the time you hit the chains (although the last part is more like a scramble).
content.location: Rock-A-Bye Baby goes up the obvious arete on the east wall.

content.description: Traverse up ramp on East wall.  Then head up and slightly right continuing over bulge and on to the chains.  Fun
content.location: Traverse left up obvious ramp on East face then straight up and right.

content.description: Route follows a clean crimpy face with very little chance to rest.
content.location: Located left from Unknown route and Two Minute Crack. Work up small hump then to slightly overhung clean face.
